{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"286dfdba-9295-4841-bf86-12231f9bd7bf","content":"## How it works\n\n- **No API key needed** — the `id-token: write` permission lets the runner request an OIDC token. NuGet.org validates it against your trusted publisher config (org, repo, workflow, environment).\n- `dotnet nuget push` without `--api-key` works automatically when the OIDC token is present and trusted publishing is configured.\n- Triggered on version tags (e.g., `git tag v1.0.0 && git push --tags`).\n\n## Key requirements\n\n1. The **workflow filename** (`publish.yml`) must match what you registered on nuget.org.\n2. The **environment** (`nuget`) must match.\n3. The `id-token: write` permission is mandatory.\n\nThe workflow file is at `.github/workflows/publish.yml`. Copy it into your repo and configure the NuGet.org side, and you're set.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5c4bf916-3d1a-4b83-9477-289c04ff0b91","outputTokens":208,"requestId":"140A:235A82:1B2D165:1E41CA3:69FA906A"},"id":"ba7e3af8-d343-46e5-9b40-3bbeffd72851","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:50:56.646Z","parentId":"5af1d366-cb2d-4632-ae03-3803ef9666ee"}
